> Imo, a scripted diff should not (explicitly) modify the content of .git. Mind removing the git from the first command?\n\nCurrently, if you rename files in a scripted diff or add new files, you are required to update the git index, otherwise the `git diff` command which verifies the script will fail because it doesn't see the new paths.
